DataElement.preferredName: Microarray Data Quantitation Type Data Type
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.:A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn.:A method for calculating a single datum of the matrix (e.g. raw intensity, background, error)._An indication of the form that a value will have.  Examples include string, integer, and character.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A 64-bit floating point primitive. When wrapped in an immutable Object, it is called a Double.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An expression consisting of a linear sequence of symbols (characters or words or phrases).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The type of an expression with two possible values, "true" and "false". Also, a variable of Boolean type or a function with Boolean arguments or result. The most common Boolean functions are AND, OR and NOT. (http://foldoc.doc.ic.ac.uk/foldoc/foldoc.cgi?Boolean)
